Food was fine but service was not. We asked a more than legit question nicely and was brushed off.  Our son is allergic to eggs. When I asked if one of the kids meal contains egg, I was met with "I don't know". Not uncommon, so I asked the staff to check. Did she check or look anything up? No. Did she asked anyone? No. Says yes it contains eggs. Does grill.cheese contain eggs? Yes. (in some cases, the bread does, so that's fine)  I then asked if there was *any* menu items that doesn't have eggs? No! Seriously. If she even thought for a second she could have served a basic garden salad without dressing. Or even suggest the prepackaged chips or apple sauce that have manufacturer labeled.  I full get the risk of cross-contamination. But saying "everything has eggs" without even thinking is just plain lazy. When I go to a restaurant I expect the staffs to know what they are serving, and if unsure at least know where to check. The staff being lazy and brushing customers off is not acceptable. If a restaurant doesn't take the time to take care of customers with allergy needs (and I mean needs, not even preference), it is saying that it doesn't values its customer.  Never visiting again.
